  "title": "TAILOR (MADE-TO MEASURE GARMENT)",
  "description": "<h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><ul><li><p>Take accurate body measurements and conduct fitting sessions for made-to-measure garments (e.g., outerwear / suits).</p></li><li><p>Draft/adjust patterns and perform alterations to achieve correct fit and silhouette.</p></li><li><p>Cut fabric and assemble garments with high workmanship (lining, zipper, pockets, collars/lapels, finishing).</p></li><li><p>Troubleshoot fitting/quality issues and implement corrections efficiently.</p></li><li><p>Ensure final garments meet measurement specs, workmanship standards, and delivery timelines.</p></li><li><p>Maintain tools, machines and a clean, safe work area.</p></li></ul><h3>Requirements</h3><ul><li><p>Minimum 3 years of experience in made-to-measure / bespoke tailoring (outerwear preferred if applicable).</p></li><li><p>Strong knowledge of garment construction, fitting and finishing techniques.</p></li><li><p>Able to work independently with attention to detail and deadlines.</p></li></ul>",
